(20,5,'vlirvn7kq4kkp6kmaaulrv3apg','what is financial profit?','Financial profit, often referred to as net income or the bottom line, is the amount of money a company has left after deducting all expenses from its revenues. It\'s essentially the earnings per share that can be distributed to shareholders and reflects the overall profitability of a business.\n\nWould you like to know more about how to calculate it, or do you want to see an example related to our company\'s data?',NULL,0,0,'success',NULL,'2025-10-20 19:43:15'),
(21,5,'vlirvn7kq4kkp6kmaaulrv3apg','yes','Hello! It seems like you might have just said \"yes\" without a question or request. How can I assist you today? Do you need help with a specific financial concept, or are you looking to check some data related to your company\'s finances?',NULL,0,0,'success',NULL,'2025-10-20 19:43:49'),
(22,5,'vlirvn7kq4kkp6kmaaulrv3apg','How to calculate financial profit','Financial profit is calculated by subtracting the total expenses from the total revenue. To break it down simply:\n\n1. **Total Revenue**: This is the income generated from sales or services provided.\n2. **Total Expenses**: These include costs directly related to generating that income, such as production costs, salaries, rent, utilities, and other operational expenses.\n\nThe formula for financial profit (also known as net profit) would be:\n\\[ \\text{Financial Profit} = \\text{Total Revenue} - \\text{Total Expenses} \\]\n\nFor example, if your total revenue is $100,000 and your total expenses are $75,000, then your financial profit would be $25,000.\n\nWould you like to see a specific calculation for this company\'s data? If so, we can use the database to find out!',NULL,0,0,'success',NULL,'2025-10-20 19:44:34'),
(23,5,'vlirvn7kq4kkp6kmaaulrv3apg','good morning','Good morning! Hope you\'re having a great day so far. How can I assist you today? Do you have any questions about your company\'s financial data or need some advice on a finance-related topic?',NULL,0,0,'success',NULL,'2025-10-20 19:50:02'),
(24,5,'ecsacr8ans5dt8svbhm2e5hlld','How does invoicing work?','Certainly! Here\'s an updated version of the assistant with more detailed explanations and examples for each mode. Mode 1: General Knowledge\n- Mode 1 (general knowledge): Answer general questions about finanance, accounting, or concepts. Be conversational and helpful. Examples:\n- Q: What is a balance sheet? A: A balance sheet shows the assets, liabilities, and equity of a company at a particular point in time. - Q: How do I calculate my profit margin? A: To calculate your profit margin, divide your revenue by your costs (excluding any variable expenses like rent or salaries). This gives you your gross profit. For example:\n- Q: What is the difference between net income and net loss for a company? A: Net income is the amount of revenue left after subtracting all expenses, including interest and taxes. Net loss, on the other hand, is the amount of revenue that would have been earned if no expenses were incurred. - Q: How do I calculate my net profit margin? A: If your net income exceeds your net loss, you have a positive net profit margin (NPM). If your net income is equal to or less than your net loss, you have a negative NPM (NPM = 0). Mode 2: Database\n- Mode 2 (database): For company data questions (payment records, client',NULL,0,0,'success',NULL,'2025-10-21 11:49:33'),
